Workflow of Git/Github

GitHub --> clone --> Changes--> add --> commit --> Push

clone --> through intellij/vscode
changes --> do changes in the code 
git status // to check the changes or status
git add . //adding all the files
git commit -m "msg"
git push -u origin main [step1]
or simply git push step 1 is done previously


// to push any new project from your code editor to github

git init
git remote add origin <https link>
git remote -v [to verify github user and profile]
git status // to check the changes or status
git add . //adding all the files
git commit -m "msg"
git push -u origin main [step1]
or simply git push step 1 is done previously

git reset --soft HEAD~1 //to undo commit from git [local machine]
git restore --staged file/files --> to remove file/files from staging area [if u did git add .]


------------------------ update the code from another computer/folder/dir ------------

//Get a repo for the first time
git clone <url>

//go to your project folder where .git already there

//to check origin
git remote show origin

//Download latest updates from GitHub
git pull origin main

//Save local changes to history
"git commit -m ""message"""

//Upload local changes to GitHub
git push origin main
